The '''coin pouch glitch''' was a major [[glitch]] that occurred after a [[Update:Game Integrity: Pickpocketing|game update]] on [[12 July]] [[2018]].

The code which handles death in game was changed in the update in order to accommodate the [[coin pouch]],{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1017387121454305286|date=12 July 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/gHvef|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=Someone was updating the death code to handle the new thieving pouches, and they kinda did it wrong.}} but was done incorrectly{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1017380655276154882|date=12 July 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/R6PPA|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=Looks to me like someone was trying to write a check to avoid overflowing max int, and they did it very wrong.}} and wasn't set up to handle stacks of other items,{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1017376520921407490|date=12 July 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/GkPDB|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=The death handling of the new pouch item wasn't set up to handle stacks of any other item.}} which caused certain items in a player's inventory to become a stack of {{formatexpr|2^31-1}} [[coins]]. This {{WP|2,147,483,647#In computing|number}} is the maximum value a 32-bit signed integer can take, which is the data type ''RuneScape'' uses for item quantity.

[[Jagex]] immediately took action by taking the Old School [[server]]s offline on 11:54 (UTC) after announcing to do so five minutes earlier,{{CiteTwitter|author=Old School RuneScape|url=https://twitter.com/OldSchoolRS/status/1017360323068792832|date=12 July 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/IyDsC|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=We're turning Old School RuneScape off for a while whilst we investigate a potential issue. Apologies for any inconvenience, we'll return service as soon as we're able to!}} around 20 minutes after the update went live. Hours after the glitch occurred, Jagex announced they were performing restoration (a [[rollback]]) of the game.{{CiteForum|author = Mod Sween|url = http://services.runescape.com/m=news/old-school-runescape-status-update?oldschool=1|title = Old School RuneScape Status Update|forum = Old School RuneScape|postdate = [[12 July]] [[2018]]}}{{CiteGeneral|url=https://support.runescape.com/hc/en-gb/articles/360001299169--12-July-Old-School-RuneScape-Offline|author=Jagex|title=(12-July) Old School RuneScape Offline|date=12 July 2018|archiveurl=https://perma.cc/H4N3-SAPC|archivedate=12 July 2018}}

After the rollback was finished and the servers were made online again, Jagex said they would be removing membership from [[account]]s that illegitimately acquired it from purchasing [[Old school bond|bonds]] via money produced from the glitch. They also said those who abused it would be [[ban|temporarily removed from the game]].

